Key Match Events: Jaxson Hayes delivered big for the Lakers, executing a monster dunk with under three minutes left in the third quarter and scoring 12 points, grabbing six rebounds, and having a +21 plus-minus.
Post-Match Reflections: Head coach JJ Redick praised Jaxson Hayes for stepping up to the moment and delivering a strong performance without Anthony Davis.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Lakers outscored the Raptors 70-48 in the second half, cruising to victory.
Others: LeBron James found Hayes repeatedly for lobs, and Austin Reaves praised Hayes' game, calling it one of his best since joining the team.
